  "texts": [
    "Similarly, Li et al. (2023) proposed a framework that incorporates multi-scale features, including handcrafted features, sentence-level features, document-level features and prompt-relevance features.",
    "As it is shown in Fig. 10, document-level features are extracted using LSTM with average pooling as proposed by Taghipour and Ng (2016), while the sentence-level features are captured by employing sentence-BERT (SBERT) on the essay, followed by LSTM with attention pooling.",
    "Prompt adherence is computed by comparing the prompt and essay representations for similarity.",
    "The method employs Doc2Vec to represent prompts and essays, using cosine similarity to measure the degree of relevance.",
    "The handcrafted features include aspects like grammatical correctness, text richness and other length-based features."
